Job Description:
1.Scope of working:

- Performance Management Officer:  is responsible in staff evaluation and bonus calculation, develop and coordinate policies and strategies for the development of performance indicator.

2.Duties & responsibilities:
- Analyze performance evaluation to address the concern and recommended PIP (Performance improvement Plan);
- Contribute to Probation evaluation by maintaining employee’s probation master list as well as other information with all relevant department;
- Contribute to all reward and recognition practices;
- Contribute to LEO (Leave Early Overtime) report and LWN (Leave Without Notification);
- Involve in calculation bonus and other commission in accordance to the policy and procedures;
- Involve in exit interview, maintain master list and other clearance;
- Other tasks assigned by Manager.


3.Qualification & requirement:
- Bachelor or Master degree in business administration or other relevant fields;
- At least 1 year of working experience;
- Proficiency in Microsoft Office and Financial Software;
- Good oral and written both English and Khmer;
- Good analytical, management, interpersonal and problem solving skills;
- Be friendly, flexible, honest, hard-working and willing to work as a team;
- Be a detail oriented, a problem solver and able to work under pressure with high responsibility.

RESPONSIBILITIES/DUTIES

- Project management

- Manage and oversee the project and ensure that the project activities will be implemented smoothly; 
- Working with project team to develop work plan, budget plan and implement; 
- Monitor the project progress, both activities and expenditures;
- Produce the outcome of both activities and expenditure and report to the management team for review and approval; 
b) Project implementation
- Establish cases referral system;
- Work with project team to develop the advocacy campaign strategy;
- Build or strengthen networking and communication with key stakeholders at all levels, including government institutions, private sectors, NGOs, ect… at local, sub-national, national and regional, to seek their support for the project implementation, including cases referral and advocacy work;
- Liaise with Government institutions and other partners to strengthen cases referral system and advocacy initiative;
- Working with national consultant and members of Technical - Working Group (TWG) to advocate and lobby the Royal - - --- Government of Cambodia to review the Law on the Suppression of Human Trafficking and Sexual Exploitation (TIP law);
- Work closely with lawyers, polices and local authorities;
Organize training, workshop and awareness raising session;
- Attend court hearing;
- Attend meeting, workshop and conference all at national, regional and international levels;
- Able to travel to the province, regional and international levels;
Other tasks may require.
